  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "\r\nUsing one value and only strings as suggested I get zero results. \r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1690659/39624545-a7bc940a-4f91-11e8-9367-d9d1a36a7f23.png)\r\n\r\nUsing one value and only booleans like so:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1690659/39624538-a265a3a2-4f91-11e8-95f7-b10f351294c2.png)\r\n\r\nI get the following error:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1690659/39624537-9e7fe590-4f91-11e8-807e-610597325b84.png)\r\n\r\nAlthough I do get results but they are not filtered as expected and the widgets appear mangled\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1690659/39624795-875f539a-4f92-11e8-88b2-d40647669dbf.png)\r\n\r\nNot using any initial configuration the filtering / toggling widgets work correctly but I need an initial filtering for my use case.\r\n\r\nStarting to feel that instantsearch comes with too much magic. Is there a web client for doing all refinement myself?\r\n\r\nThank you for reading",
